Load ITS2 datasets using NCBI (Dubois) database taxonomy assignment

ps_pollen <- readRDS(paste0(dataDir, "/ps_ITS2_DB4_derep_geoRestricted.rds"))

ps_pollen_filt <- ps_pollen %>%
    subset_taxa(!is.na(Genus)) %>%
    subset_samples(!is.na(Fruitcrop) & Rep_ID ==
        1 & !is.na(Order) & Lab_code_rep != "CA17")
ps_pollen_filt
## phyloseq-class experiment-level object

# remove taxa with zero counts
ps_pollen_filt <- prune_taxa(taxa_sums(ps_pollen_filt) >
    0, ps_pollen_filt)

tax <- data.frame(tax_table(ps_pollen_filt))

tax[is.na(tax)] <- "NA"

for (i in 1:nrow(tax)) {
    if (tax[i, 2] == "NA") {
        kingdom <- paste("Kingdom_", tax[i, 1],
            sep = "")
        tax[i, 2:7] <- kingdom
    } else if (tax[i, 3] == "NA") {
        phylum <- paste("Phylum_", tax[i, 2],
            sep = "")
        tax[i, 3:7] <- phylum
    } else if (tax[i, 4] == "NA") {
        class <- paste("Class_", tax[i, 3], sep = "")
        tax[i, 4:7] <- class
    } else if (tax[i, 5] == "NA") {
        order <- paste("Order_", tax[i, 4], sep = "")
        tax[i, 5:7] <- order
    } else if (tax[i, 6] == "NA") {
        family <- paste("Family_", tax[i, 5],
            sep = "")
        tax[i, 6:7] <- family
    } else if ((tax[i, 7] == "NA" | tax[i, 7] ==
        "sp" | tax[i, 7] == "sp.")) {
        tax$Species[i] <- paste("Genus_", tax[i,
            6], sep = "")
    } else if (tax[i, 7] == "NA") {
    }
}

tax_table(ps_pollen_filt) <- as.matrix(tax)

tax_visitors[is.na(tax_visitors)] <- "NA"

Replace NA with highest taxonomic assinment

for (i in 1:nrow(tax_visitors)) {
    if (tax_visitors[i, 2] == "NA") {
        order <- paste("Order_", tax_visitors[i,
            1], sep = "")
        tax_visitors[i, 2:4] <- order
    } else if (tax_visitors[i, 3] == "NA") {
        family <- paste("Family_", tax_visitors[i,
            2], sep = "")
        tax_visitors[i, 3:4] <- family
    } else if ((tax_visitors[i, 4] == "NA")) {
        tax_visitors$Lowest_assignment[i] <- paste("Genus_",
            tax_visitors[i, 2], sep = "")
    } else if (tax_visitors[i, 4] == "NA") {
    }
}

Tree map fruit crop

tax_df <- tax_table(ps_pollen_filt_Species) %>%
    data.frame %>%
    group_by(Family, Genus, Species) %>%
    summarise(dummy = n_distinct(Genus)) %>%
    data.frame %>%
    select(Family, Genus, Species) %>%
    mutate(Genus_species = paste(Genus, Species,
        sep = "_"))

tax_df$Genus_species <- str_replace(tax_df$Genus_species,
    pattern = ".?Genus+.*", replacement = "_sp.")

# frecuency data frame according to fruit
# crop

pollen_freq_df <- as.data.frame(asv_species_to_incidence_fruitcrop)
pollen_freq_df$Genus_species <- rownames(pollen_freq_df)
names(pollen_freq_df)
## [1] "Persea americana" "Malus domestica"  "Prunus domestica" "Rubus"           
## [5] "Genus_species"
pollen_freq_df$overall_freq <- rowSums(pollen_freq_df[,
    1:4])
pollen_freq_df <- pollen_freq_df %>%
    pivot_longer(cols = c("Persea americana":"Rubus"),
        names_to = "Fruitcrop", values_to = "freq")
sample_totals <- data.frame(table(sample_data(pollen_hier_crop)$Fruitcrop))
names(sample_totals) <- c("Fruitcrop", "n_samples")
pollen_freq_df <- left_join(pollen_freq_df, sample_totals,
    by = "Fruitcrop")
pollen_freq_df$overall_prevalence <- pollen_freq_df$overall_freq/nrow(sample_data(ps_pollen_filt_Species))
pollen_freq_df$perfruitcrop_prevalence <- pollen_freq_df$freq/nrow(sample_data(ps_pollen_filt_Species))

pollen_freq_df <- left_join(pollen_freq_df, tax_df,
    by = "Genus_species")

pollen_freq_df$Genus_species_cutoff <- ifelse(pollen_freq_df$overall_prevalence >
    0.2, pollen_freq_df$Genus_species, " ")
pollen_freq_df$Genus_species_cutoff <- str_replace(pollen_freq_df$Genus_species_cutoff,
    "_", " ")


# Update taxonomy: Viburnum costaricanum

tax_df <- tax_table(ps_pollen_filt_Species) %>%
    data.frame %>%
    group_by(Family, Genus, Species) %>%
    summarise(dummy = n_distinct(Genus)) %>%
    data.frame %>%
    select(Family, Genus, Species) %>%
    mutate(Genus_species = paste(Genus, Species,
        sep = "_"))

tax_df$Genus_species <- str_replace(tax_df$Genus_species,
    pattern = ".?Genus+.*", replacement = "_sp.")

# frecuency data frame according to insect
# group

pollen_freq_df <- as.data.frame(asv_species_to_incidence_bichos)
pollen_freq_df$Genus_species <- rownames(pollen_freq_df)
names(pollen_freq_df)
## [1] "Bombus"        "Apis"          "Non-Syrphidae" "Other"        
## [5] "Syrphidae"     "Genus_species"
pollen_freq_df$overall_freq <- rowSums(pollen_freq_df[,
    1:4])
pollen_freq_df <- pollen_freq_df %>%
    pivot_longer(cols = c("Bombus":"Syrphidae"),
        names_to = "Bichos_group", values_to = "freq")
sample_totals <- data.frame(table(sample_data(pollen_hier_crop)$Bichos_group))
names(sample_totals) <- c("Bichos_group", "n_samples")
pollen_freq_df <- left_join(pollen_freq_df, sample_totals,
    by = "Bichos_group")
pollen_freq_df$overall_prevalence <- pollen_freq_df$overall_freq/nrow(sample_data(ps_pollen_filt_Species))
pollen_freq_df$perbichos_prevalence <- pollen_freq_df$freq/nrow(sample_data(ps_pollen_filt_Species))

pollen_freq_df <- left_join(pollen_freq_df, tax_df,
    by = "Genus_species")


pollen_freq_df$Genus_species_cutoff <- ifelse(pollen_freq_df$overall_prevalence >
    0.2, pollen_freq_df$Genus_species, " ")
pollen_freq_df$Genus_species_cutoff <- str_replace(pollen_freq_df$Genus_species_cutoff,
    "_", " ")

# Update taxonomy: Viburnum costaricanum
# (Viburnaceae), este cambi de familia,
# antes en Adoxaceae

pollen_freq_df$Family <- ifelse(pollen_freq_df$Genus_species_cutoff ==
    "Viburnum costaricanum", "Viburnaceae", pollen_freq_df$Family)

pollen_freq_df$Bichos_group <- ifelse(pollen_freq_df$Bichos_group ==
    "Non-Syrphidae", "Non-Syr", pollen_freq_df$Bichos_group)
